T1  - FSLIC assistance and the wealth effects of savings and loan acquisitions
AU  - Gupta, Atul
AU  - LeCompte, Richard L.B.
AU  - Misra, Lalatendu
JO  - Journal of Monetary Economics
VL  - 31
IS  - 1
SP  - 117
EP  - 128
PY  - 1993
DA  - 1993/02/01/
SN  - 0304-3932
DO  - https://doi.org/10.1016/0304-3932(93)90019-C
UR  - https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/030439329390019C
AB  - This paper examines whether FSLIC-assisted failed thrift mergers in the 1980s resulted in wealth transfers from the insurance fund to acquiring firm stockholders. We find that winning bidders earned positive abnormal returns upon the announcement of such mergers. More importantly, the abnormal returns are larger in cases where the FSLIC provided direct financial assistance, and bidder abnormal returns are positively related to the size of FSLIC assistance. These results suggest that the process followed by the FSLIC in arranging failed thrift mergers did result in wealth transfers.
ER  - 
